my son needs help right now.

12:21.237 --> 12:22.537
- Get your hands off me.
- Look!

12:22.539 --> 12:24.472
- Call in security.
- Sir? Doctor.

12:24.474 --> 12:26.307
I'm sorry,
my son is throwing up.

12:26.309 --> 12:28.376
It's fucking green,
and he's in real pain! Please.

12:28.378 --> 12:30.377
What's wrong with him?
What's wrong with him?

12:30.379 --> 12:33.047
- [groans] Stop, no!
- Get me a gurney.

12:33.049 --> 12:35.415
Here. I'll take him.

12:35.417 --> 12:37.651
It's okay.
It's okay.

12:37.653 --> 12:40.054
You're okay.
Here we go.

12:40.056 --> 12:41.689
Come on, guys.

12:41.691 --> 12:43.090
Here we go.

12:45.760 --> 12:47.728
Watch your hands, please.

12:47.730 --> 12:49.863
- Bay four. Let's go.
- Come on.

12:49.865 --> 12:51.898
Excuse us.

12:51.900 --> 12:54.367
[groans] Ow.

12:54.369 --> 12:56.035
It's okay, sweetheart.

12:56.037 --> 12:58.305
- Stop!
- Shh. Shh. Okay.

12:58.307 --> 13:00.574
This hasn't been the best day
of your life, has it?

13:00.576 --> 13:02.609
- I'm gonna puke again.
- Okay.

13:02.611 --> 13:05.144
If you've got to puke, go ahead.
Nurse Reagan's armed and ready.

13:05.146 --> 13:06.580
Now tell me which is worse.

13:06.582 --> 13:08.415
- If I poke here...
- Ow.

13:08.417 --> 13:09.816
- Or here?
- [inhales sharply] Ow!

13:09.818 --> 13:11.483
Okay, I'm done.
I'm done poking you.

13:11.485 --> 13:13.319
- What is it? His appendix?
- Just one moment, Dad.

13:13.321 --> 13:15.487
Sussman's coming down?
Good. The next room's ours.

13:15.489 --> 13:16.789
- Are you operating?
- What?

13:16.791 --> 13:18.224
- Mom.
- It's all right, honey.

13:18.226 --> 13:20.093
They're gonna help you.
He seems very nice.

13:20.095 --> 13:23.429
I try. Listen, buddy,
we know how to fix this,

13:23.431 --> 13:25.098
and I'm gonna walk you
through everything.

13:25.100 --> 13:26.632
Now first I'm gonna
check in with your parents,

13:26.634 --> 13:29.435
and then we'll be right back.
Okay?

13:29.437 --> 13:32.705
Okay, did you hear him?
He said they know how to fix it.

13:32.707 --> 13:34.139
- Okay?
- Mom, I'm scared.

13:34.141 --> 13:36.574
Sweetheart, I love you
very, very much.

13:36.576 --> 13:38.043
[Noah] Helen.

13:38.045 --> 13:40.112
Come on.

13:40.114 --> 13:42.981
- [groans]
- Hang in there, okay?

13:42.983 --> 13:44.816
Hang in there.

13:44.818 --> 13:46.818
[Ullah] It's looking like Martin
has a perforated bowel.

13:46.820 --> 13:47.819
Looking like?
What does that mean?

13:47.821 --> 13:49.420
Let him finish.

13:49.422 --> 13:50.922
I can feel a swollen abscess
I'm going to clean out.

13:50.924 --> 13:52.791
Now, there's a lot
that could have caused this.

13:52.793 --> 13:54.592
Once we get in there,
we'll know more.

13:54.594 --> 13:56.527
- The symptoms started when?
- Two months ago.

13:56.529 --> 13:58.062
- Three months ago.
- No, it hasn't been that long.

13:58.064 --> 13:59.797
Yes, it's obvious
if you were paying attention.

13:59.799 --> 14:01.366
What about food?
Is he eating?

14:01.368 --> 14:02.767
- Not well.
- He's lost some weight.

14:02.769 --> 14:04.269
Uh, today.
Breakfast? Lunch?

14:04.271 --> 14:05.803
He's had two hot dogs
and some popcorn.

14:05.805 --> 14:07.472
- Two hot dogs?
- We were at a ball game.

14:07.474 --> 14:09.006
I asked you to watch
what he was eating.

14:09.008 --> 14:11.041
- I was glad he was eating.
- Folks, folks.

14:11.043 --> 14:13.311
I know this is hard,
but let's try to keep cool here.

14:13.313 --> 14:15.446
I'd say the surgery
should run about two hours,

14:15.448 --> 14:16.881
possibly longer
if we run into...

14:16.883 --> 14:18.015
Doctor,
there's a room available.

14:18.017 --> 14:20.016
All right,
let's prep him then.

14:20.018 --> 14:22.152
- Right now?
- Right now.

14:24.622 --> 14:26.956
Okay, Martin, we're gonna
put you to sleep for a bit,

14:26.958 --> 14:28.525
but when you wake up,
you'll feel much better.

14:28.527 --> 14:30.427
Mom, what's going on?
I'm having surgery?

14:30.429 --> 14:32.529
Yeah, but it's gonna be fine.
I promise, honey.

14:32.531 --> 14:34.765
I'm giving you some medicine
to help you relax.

14:34.767 --> 14:37.167
- Dad?
- It's gonna be okay.

14:37.169 --> 14:38.968
- I'll come see you right after.
- Thank you.

14:38.970 --> 14:41.370
[Dr. Sussman] Okay,
we're gonna go inside now.

14:41.372 --> 14:43.272
You guys coming too?

14:43.274 --> 14:44.873
No, honey,
we can't go in with you.

14:44.875 --> 14:46.342
Tell you what, buddy.

14:46.344 --> 14:47.643
Where do you want to go
for vacation next?

14:47.645 --> 14:49.612
- You get to decide.
- Not Montauk.

14:49.614 --> 14:51.213
No,
definitely not Montauk.

14:51.215 --> 14:53.882
- Anywhere you want to go.
- Hawaii?

14:53.884 --> 14:55.384
- Yeah.
- We'll learn to surf.

14:55.386 --> 14:56.819
We can get
a house on the beach.

14:56.821 --> 15:00.122
Okay, say aloha, Mom and Dad.
See you soon.

15:00.124 --> 15:01.957
[both] Aloha.

15:07.363 --> 15:09.798
[elevator bell dings]

15:13.102 --> 15:16.371
[indistinct chatter]

15:16.373 --> 15:18.307
Psychosomatic, huh?

15:32.421 --> 15:33.588
[Noah]
They told me it was two hours.

15:33.590 --> 15:36.123
He's been in there for three...

15:44.166 --> 15:47.101
[indistinct chatter]

15:48.337 --> 15:50.271
[phone rings]

16:05.453 --> 16:07.388
How many times
have you called her?

16:07.390 --> 16:11.592
I left her two messages.

16:11.594 --> 16:14.227
- She's a nurse.
- She's a waitress.

16:14.229 --> 16:15.763
She's a pediatric nurse
who might be able

16:15.765 --> 16:17.964
to tell us something,
give us some fucking information

16:17.966 --> 16:20.133
since no one else
will come talk to us.

16:20.135 --> 16:21.668
If we'd listened to her
in the first place,

16:21.670 --> 16:23.169
none of this
would've happened.

16:23.171 --> 16:24.638
What is that supposed to mean?

16:24.640 --> 16:25.739
She said bring him
to the hospital

16:25.741 --> 16:27.974
that first day he was bad.

16:27.976 --> 16:29.742
The day you lost your mind.

16:29.744 --> 16:31.244
I did not lose my mind!
I made a mistake!

16:31.246 --> 16:32.845
Instead you took him
to a shrink

16:32.847 --> 16:34.014
because your mother said
it was my fault...

16:34.016 --> 16:35.481
You know what,
this isn't fair.

16:35.483 --> 16:36.749
...I caused his problems,
I made him sick.

16:36.751 --> 16:38.484
This is not fair!
Noah, it is not fair.

16:38.486 --> 16:40.353
- I mean, Helen, I know...
- Are you actually blaming me?

16:40.355 --> 16:42.088
I know you're angry with me, but
the way you ate up all that crap

16:42.090 --> 16:43.756
she was spoon-feeding you
when everyone else can see...

16:43.758 --> 16:45.558
You're the one that took him
to the fucking baseball game

16:45.560 --> 16:46.927
- and just fed him all of that...
- ...she's a raving lunatic?

16:46.929 --> 16:48.061
When are you gonna learn
to think for yourself?

16:48.063 --> 16:50.930
[Ullah]
You can stop now.

16:50.932 --> 16:54.400
Martin's okay.
It went well.

16:54.402 --> 16:55.635
[sighs]

16:55.637 --> 16:57.570
- Why don't you sit too?
- Yeah.

17:02.208 --> 17:04.844
So we removed a length
of Martin's bowel

17:04.846 --> 17:06.813
that was perforated
and infected.

17:06.815 --> 17:08.647
I'm guessing
it's Crohn's disease.

17:08.650 --> 17:10.983
- And what is that?
- It's an autoimmune disease.

17:10.984 --> 17:13.952
Autoimmune, um...

17:13.954 --> 17:15.954
It's like your mom.

17:18.156 --> 17:19.790
Yeah, my mom had MS.

17:19.792 --> 17:20.858
That makes sense.

17:20.861 --> 17:22.193
The diseases are related.

17:22.194 --> 17:23.662
They can show up
in the same family.

17:23.664 --> 17:26.464
Well, he's seen his doctor
twice.

17:26.467 --> 17:28.467
Crohn's is notoriously hard
to diagnose.

17:28.469 --> 17:29.968
It can look like
all kinds of things.

17:29.970 --> 17:31.235
So what now?

17:31.237 --> 17:33.338
Martin will stay here
for ten days.

17:33.340 --> 17:34.673
You'll meet with my colleague,

17:34.675 --> 17:36.007
and she'll talk you
through everything.

17:36.009 --> 17:37.475
The long and the short
of it is,

17:37.477 --> 17:39.477
this is chronic
but treatable.

17:39.479 --> 17:41.412
Now, it's going to take
coordination,

17:41.414 --> 17:43.081
a lot of attention
from both of you,

17:43.083 --> 17:44.748
especially with an adolescent
who doesn't like

17:44.750 --> 17:46.817
to take medication
and misses French fries,

17:46.819 --> 17:50.855
but if you stay on him,
work together,

17:50.857 --> 17:54.325
Martin will lead
a normal life.

17:54.327 --> 17:55.693
Mm-hmm.

17:55.695 --> 17:58.629
He'll be in room 730
in about 20 minutes.

18:00.565 --> 18:02.466
- I wish you the best of luck.
- Thank you.

18:02.468 --> 18:03.467
Thank you.

18:03.469 --> 18:05.268
Sure.

18:05.270 --> 18:06.269
[sighs]

18:06.271 --> 18:08.638
[inhales sharply]

18:08.640 --> 18:10.573
[clears throat]

18:19.617 --> 18:22.519
[cell phone vibrating]

18:23.621 --> 18:25.722
[typing]

18:25.724 --> 18:28.725
<i>[♪ soft music]</i>

18:28.727 --> 18:33.663
<i>♪</i>

18:51.047 --> 18:53.114
You can call her back.

18:57.687 --> 18:59.621
Thanks.
I'll try later.

19:03.092 --> 19:05.027
I don't want
to do this anymore.

19:08.097 --> 19:09.865
I can't fight with you anymore.

19:09.867 --> 19:11.967
It has to stop.

19:14.503 --> 19:15.804
I hate this fucking divorce.

19:15.806 --> 19:17.973
I just want it over.

19:17.975 --> 19:21.142
I want to go back
to mediation,

19:21.144 --> 19:23.078
and I'll give you
whatever you want.

19:33.255 --> 19:36.091
[sighs]
Helen, all I want is co-custody.

19:36.093 --> 19:38.025
I know.

19:41.497 --> 19:43.431
You should have that.

19:45.334 --> 19:48.169
[sighs]

19:48.171 --> 19:50.105
And you can have
her too.

19:52.774 --> 19:55.375
'Cause we have to do better.
I have...

19:55.377 --> 19:57.311
I have to do better.

19:59.781 --> 20:01.682
And I will.

20:04.486 --> 20:07.121
You're an excellent father.

20:16.765 --> 20:18.099
Thank you.

20:22.004 --> 20:24.939
[sighs]

20:26.674 --> 20:28.942
So call her back.

20:28.944 --> 20:30.810
- Oh, it's okay.
- No, really.

20:30.812 --> 20:32.746
Please, I want you to.

20:37.185 --> 20:38.118
[Noah chuckles]

20:41.088 --> 20:42.689
Hey, sweetie.

20:42.691 --> 20:44.924
Hey, buddy.
How you feel?

20:44.926 --> 20:45.925
You okay?

20:45.927 --> 20:47.961
Hey, honey, you awake?

20:47.963 --> 20:51.431
[sighs]

20:51.433 --> 20:52.466
Who won the game?

20:52.468 --> 20:54.801
[both chuckle]

20:54.803 --> 20:57.136
Baltimore.
You didn't miss anything.

20:57.138 --> 20:59.605
[exhales]

20:59.607 --> 21:00.706
[chuckles]

21:02.376 --> 21:04.943
[sighs]

21:39.011 --> 21:40.978
[sighs]

21:45.050 --> 21:46.718
How is he?

21:46.720 --> 21:48.853
- He's okay.
- [sighs]

21:48.855 --> 21:51.255
He's gonna be okay.

21:51.257 --> 21:52.690
Is he upstairs?

21:52.692 --> 21:54.692
No, he's still
at the hospital.

21:54.694 --> 21:57.528
Noah's with him.

21:57.530 --> 21:59.931
Noah's with him?

21:59.933 --> 22:02.399
That's correct.

22:02.401 --> 22:03.834
I need to go to sleep.

22:03.836 --> 22:05.836
Jesus.

22:05.838 --> 22:08.405
Helen, how could you
be so stupid?

22:08.407 --> 22:10.407
Good night, Mom.

22:10.409 --> 22:12.943
I knew I should've gone
to the hospital with you.

22:12.945 --> 22:15.646
Your father and I
are going to great expense

22:15.648 --> 22:17.781
to prove that Noah
is an unfit father.

22:17.783 --> 22:21.385
Then you leave him alone
with Martin voluntarily?

22:21.387 --> 22:23.654
What kind of message
does that send to Judge Polk?

22:23.656 --> 22:25.988
We're in the middle of a
custody battle, for God's sakes.

22:25.990 --> 22:28.190
Actually, we're not anymore.

22:30.261 --> 22:32.495
We're splitting custody.
We've agreed.

22:32.497 --> 22:35.164
Helen, I can't let you
do that.

22:35.166 --> 22:37.333
I think you're making
a terrible mistake,

22:37.335 --> 22:38.901
an irreversible,
irresponsible...

22:38.903 --> 22:42.138
I don't fucking care
what you think!

22:42.140 --> 22:45.575
My son almost died today
because I listened to you!

22:45.577 --> 22:47.443
- Oh, for God's sake.
- Oh, yes!

22:47.445 --> 22:50.111
You kept insisting
it was all in his head

22:50.113 --> 22:53.282
and made me feel like
a pathetic, crazy...

22:53.284 --> 22:55.984
And the whole time
it was so obvious

22:55.986 --> 22:58.920
he was very, very sick.

23:00.657 --> 23:02.991
And I listened to you.

23:02.993 --> 23:05.727
I always fucking
listen to you,

23:05.729 --> 23:08.963
and you talk,
and you talk, and you talk

23:08.965 --> 23:11.333
until your voice
is the only thing in my head

23:11.335 --> 23:13.769
and I cannot
even think straight.

23:16.138 --> 23:17.738
You're right.

23:17.740 --> 23:20.008
You're too tired
to have this conversation.

23:20.010 --> 23:22.610
Go to bed.

23:44.999 --> 23:47.468
You wanted
my marriage to fail.

23:47.470 --> 23:49.069
What?

23:49.071 --> 23:53.507
You wanted
my marriage to fail...

23:53.509 --> 23:55.943
because yours was a sham
and you were jealous.

24:01.616 --> 24:04.719
I loved him...

24:04.721 --> 24:06.354
so much.

24:06.356 --> 24:08.255
I loved him...

24:08.257 --> 24:12.192
for who he was,
and you convinced me

24:12.194 --> 24:14.261
that he wasn't enough,
so I hope you're happy

24:14.263 --> 24:17.030
now that
you've ruined everything...

24:17.032 --> 24:19.399
my marriage,
my entire life.

24:19.401 --> 24:21.368
[sniffles]

24:21.370 --> 24:23.737
I realize this has been a very
difficult evening for you.

24:23.739 --> 24:26.840
Yeah,
I want you to leave.

24:28.076 --> 24:31.011
- What?
- I hate you.

24:31.013 --> 24:33.847
I really do.

24:33.849 --> 24:36.350
And I want you
to get out of my house.

24:40.553 --> 24:42.688
I said leave.

24:44.391 --> 24:47.393
<i>[♪ soft music]</i>

24:47.395 --> 24:52.331
<i>♪</i>

25:09.749 --> 25:11.249
[sighs]

25:27.333 --> 25:30.168
Your father's divorcing me.

25:30.170 --> 25:32.537
He told me after you left.

25:38.110 --> 25:40.245
I'm sorry to hear that.

25:50.288 --> 25:51.622
[car door opens]

25:57.195 --> 25:59.363
[car doors close]

25:59.365 --> 26:02.433
[engine starts]

26:04.235 --> 26:05.837
[sighs]

26:14.044 --> 26:17.213
- [Whitney] Is Martin okay?
- Yeah.

26:17.215 --> 26:19.449
Are you okay?

26:23.187 --> 26:26.122
[crying]

26:45.742 --> 26:49.379
Did you find anything
during discovery?

26:49.381 --> 26:51.381
Look at you,
getting all technical.

26:51.383 --> 26:52.915
You've been reading up.

26:52.917 --> 26:55.885
Well, he's the father
of my children, Jon.

26:55.887 --> 26:58.554
Yes, you're right.
Of course.

26:58.556 --> 27:01.823
I got a lead recently
from a guy who claims

27:01.825 --> 27:03.791
to have a piece of evidence
that could

27:03.793 --> 27:05.293
blow this whole case wide open.

27:05.295 --> 27:06.294
Who?

27:06.296 --> 27:08.130
You know I'm not allowed

27:08.132 --> 27:10.232
to talk about all the details
of this case with you, Helen.

27:10.234 --> 27:12.067
Well,
what can you talk about?

27:12.069 --> 27:15.370
Was it a witness?
Did he see it happen?

27:15.372 --> 27:17.705
No, he says he has
something on the victim

27:17.707 --> 27:19.607
that we will want to see.

27:19.609 --> 27:22.077
On Scott Lockhart?

27:22.079 --> 27:24.279
Why doesn't he just
call the police?

27:24.281 --> 27:26.314
The police won't pay him.

27:30.285 --> 27:32.920
But if they find his evidence,
they can subpoena it

27:32.922 --> 27:36.090
and use it, right?

27:36.092 --> 27:38.025
Are you looking
for a job here?

27:40.228 --> 27:41.462
How much does he want?

27:41.464 --> 27:42.996
100K.

27:48.303 --> 27:49.970
I'll pay it.

27:52.740 --> 27:56.710
Are you sure? A, and, B,
are you sure you can?

27:56.712 --> 27:58.712
I'll sell the house.
I'll make it work.

27:58.714 --> 28:00.714
You have to get him off
no matter what.

28:04.786 --> 28:06.687
[sighs]

28:06.689 --> 28:09.990
I understand.
Thank you.

28:09.992 --> 28:12.158
Is that it?

28:12.160 --> 28:13.794
That's it.

28:13.796 --> 28:16.797
<i>[♪ dramatic music]</i>

28:16.799 --> 28:21.702
<i>♪</i>

28:36.650 --> 28:40.052
Mary, get me Oscar Hodges
on the phone, please.

28:43.454 --> 28:46.505
_

28:51.030 --> 28:52.631
[groans]

29:08.748 --> 29:12.451
[coffee grinder whirs]

29:28.200 --> 29:30.535
- Hi, Daddy.
- Hey.

29:30.537 --> 29:33.237
Did Mommy
go to the hospital?

29:33.239 --> 29:35.173
Yeah, it was her turn.

29:40.278 --> 29:42.379
What happened
to the Bisquick?

29:42.381 --> 29:44.381
What?
Oh, I don't know.

29:44.383 --> 29:47.150
- Can we watch TV?
- Sure.

29:56.527 --> 29:59.596
- Here.
- All right.

29:59.598 --> 30:02.064
All right,
tape, please.

30:02.066 --> 30:03.332
[door opens]

30:03.334 --> 30:04.933
Hey, who drew
that Yankees logo?

30:04.935 --> 30:06.335
- I did.
- What?

30:06.337 --> 30:07.503
It wasn't done
by a professional?

30:07.505 --> 30:08.904
[door closes]

30:08.906 --> 30:10.172
[Whitney] Can someone
help me with this?

30:10.174 --> 30:11.773
Coming.

30:11.775 --> 30:15.678
I found a gluten-free,
sugar-free, vegan cake!

30:15.680 --> 30:17.680
I'd rather eat
my own foot fungus.

30:17.682 --> 30:20.115
Good thing it's not for you,
stupid head.

30:20.117 --> 30:22.550
It's for Martin,
whose stomach is extra delicate.

30:22.552 --> 30:24.485
- He's gonna hate it.
- Whoop.

30:26.555 --> 30:28.556
- Hey, Dad?
- Yeah, buddy?

30:28.558 --> 30:30.425
How about we get
Martin a dog?

30:30.427 --> 30:32.427
I really think
he would like it.

30:32.429 --> 30:34.262
Did your mom say
you could get a dog?

30:34.264 --> 30:36.664
- She said she'd think about it.
- Oh, she said no.

30:36.666 --> 30:37.932
No, she said
she'd think about it.

30:37.934 --> 30:39.400
Can we look for a dog?

30:39.402 --> 30:41.068
Yeah, Stacey wants one too.

30:41.070 --> 30:42.269
- [doorknob rattles]
- Oh, my God, they're here.

30:42.271 --> 30:43.903
What should we do?
Should we hide?

30:43.905 --> 30:45.905
- Yeah, come on. Hide.
- Okay, go, go, go, go, go.

30:45.907 --> 30:46.840
Go.

30:48.843 --> 30:49.909
[door opens]

30:49.911 --> 30:52.078
Oh!

30:52.080 --> 30:53.680
[door closes]

30:53.682 --> 30:55.315
I'm back, suckers!

30:57.051 --> 31:00.053
- Hi, Dad.
- [all] Surprise!

31:00.055 --> 31:03.856
- Welcome home.
- Thanks.

31:03.858 --> 31:06.325
- How are you? Okay?
- I'm good.

31:06.327 --> 31:09.161
- Hey.
- Dude, dude, show me your scar.

31:09.163 --> 31:10.396
You want me
to take this off?

31:10.398 --> 31:11.397
- Yeah!
- Okay, after we eat.

31:11.399 --> 31:12.732
- Whoa!
- Ugh.

31:12.734 --> 31:15.234
- Come see what we made!
- [squeals]

31:15.236 --> 31:16.469
How was the release?

31:16.471 --> 31:18.271
Good, except for
the thousands of dollars

31:18.273 --> 31:20.005
