with the insurance company.

31:20.007 --> 31:21.940
Oh.

31:21.942 --> 31:23.608
[Trevor]
Have you seen my meat?

31:23.610 --> 31:26.111
And the dragon says,
"Oh, I don't see any meat."

31:26.113 --> 31:28.647
And the man goes, "That's 'cause
it's in your belly!"

31:28.649 --> 31:31.650
- The end.
- Brilliant!

31:31.652 --> 31:34.286
Thank you.

31:34.288 --> 31:36.121
Did you make any friends
at the hospital?

31:36.123 --> 31:38.023
Yeah, I met
some nice people.

31:38.025 --> 31:39.925
- Any girls?
- Maybe.

31:39.927 --> 31:41.226
- Wait, what?
- Ooh.

31:41.228 --> 31:42.627
- You did?
- You met a girl?

31:42.629 --> 31:44.962
- Did she die?
- [Noah laughs]

31:44.964 --> 31:46.563
- [laughs]
- No.

31:46.565 --> 31:48.065
If she died,
it would've been a good story.

31:48.067 --> 31:49.333
You know,
like, years later,

31:49.335 --> 31:50.734
you could tell
your grandchildren,

31:50.736 --> 31:53.271
"I knew a girl once,
but she died."

31:53.273 --> 31:56.674
- [laughs]
- You know? What?

31:56.676 --> 31:58.776
Come on, who wants more cake?
Anybody?

31:58.778 --> 32:00.678
I think we should start
winding things down,

32:00.680 --> 32:02.046
maybe, 'cause it's Sunday.

32:02.048 --> 32:04.816
They have
to do their homework.

32:04.818 --> 32:06.483
Right.

32:11.656 --> 32:13.324
[Trevor] Yeah,
so can you show me, please?

32:13.326 --> 32:15.125
- You said you would.
- Not right now.

32:15.127 --> 32:17.961
Okay.

32:17.963 --> 32:20.864
This has been
the best ten days ever.

32:20.866 --> 32:22.700
Yeah, 'cause Martin
hasn't been here.

32:22.702 --> 32:24.635
You little bitch,
you missed me so much.

32:24.637 --> 32:26.837
Hey, just 'cause you almost died
doesn't mean

32:26.839 --> 32:28.004
you get to call
your little brother a bitch.

32:28.006 --> 32:29.306
I think it does.

32:29.308 --> 32:31.307
You guys are gonna
see your dad again soon.

32:31.309 --> 32:33.909
- Friday, right?
- Yeah, that's right.

32:33.911 --> 32:37.313
You finally get to see
my new place in Crown Heights.

32:37.315 --> 32:39.181
- Not far, is it?
- Is it big?

32:39.183 --> 32:40.817
No, it's not big,
but it's nice.

32:40.819 --> 32:42.819
- How many bedrooms?
- Two.

32:42.821 --> 32:45.521
You and Stacey in one,
me and the boys in the other.

32:45.523 --> 32:47.923
Nope, pass.

32:47.925 --> 32:49.792
Whitney,
it's just for the weekend.

32:49.794 --> 32:53.295
Nope, opt out, veto.
Thank you for playing.

32:53.297 --> 32:56.131
You know what?

32:56.133 --> 32:57.967
Stay here. I'll leave.

32:57.969 --> 32:59.701
Helen,
it'll be fine.

32:59.703 --> 33:01.636
I know,
but Marian's invited me

33:01.638 --> 33:03.405
to her house
on Shelter Island this weekend,

33:03.407 --> 33:05.074
and I haven't spent any
real time with her in years,

33:05.076 --> 33:06.075
so it's a perfect opportunity.

33:06.077 --> 33:08.978
I'm going, so stay.

33:12.048 --> 33:13.983
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

33:18.220 --> 33:21.256
Okay, bye.

33:21.258 --> 33:24.225
<i>[♪ soft music]</i>

33:24.227 --> 33:29.163
