<i>♪ You make it easy</i>

35:07.660 --> 35:11.228
<i>♪ It's a sad turn ♪</i>

35:11.230 --> 35:13.998
<i>♪ To be on your own</i>

35:14.000 --> 35:15.933
[knocks on door]

35:19.570 --> 35:21.538
[knocks on door]

35:23.441 --> 35:26.110
[peaceful music
playing on stereo]

35:26.112 --> 35:28.112
Alison?

35:28.114 --> 35:31.581
[Athena]
Noah.

35:31.583 --> 35:34.184
Noah!

35:34.186 --> 35:35.719
Hey, what are...
what are you doing here?

35:35.721 --> 35:38.022
I'm... I'm staying here.

35:39.657 --> 35:41.992
- With Alison?
- Yeah.

35:43.728 --> 35:46.696
It's a wonderful opportunity
for us to share energy.

35:46.698 --> 35:49.533
We haven't been
this attuned in years.

35:49.535 --> 35:51.668
Maybe ever.

35:53.404 --> 35:55.972
- That's great.
- Yeah.

35:58.776 --> 36:00.677
How's your son?

36:00.679 --> 36:02.646
How are his humors?

36:02.648 --> 36:05.248
His humors?
He's...

36:05.250 --> 36:07.350
Uh, he's... he's fine, Athena.
Thank you.

36:07.352 --> 36:09.485
Where... where is she?

36:09.487 --> 36:12.487
<i>[♪ soft music]</i>

36:12.489 --> 36:17.426
<i>♪</i>

37:05.807 --> 37:07.173
[chuckles]

37:07.175 --> 37:08.408
Hey, stranger.

37:08.410 --> 37:10.843
Wow, you look great.

37:10.845 --> 37:11.911
[chuckles]

37:15.949 --> 37:17.783
Oh, that's so sweet.
Thank you.

37:17.785 --> 37:19.719
Wait, I have to get
my towel.

37:23.023 --> 37:25.358
Oh, Noah,
these are my friends,

37:25.360 --> 37:27.393
Brendan and George.

37:38.972 --> 37:41.140
Doc said as long as he
takes his medicine,

37:41.142 --> 37:43.142
he should never have to go
to the hospital again.

37:43.144 --> 37:45.645
- That's great.
- It is. It really is.

37:45.647 --> 37:49.281
It was... it was touch and go
for a second, you know?

37:49.283 --> 37:51.617
And I realized that, uh...

37:54.687 --> 37:56.788
I want to apologize
for something.

37:59.159 --> 38:02.027
He-he-he nearly died.
I mean, he almost died.

38:02.029 --> 38:04.630
And, um...

38:04.632 --> 38:07.599
the whole time
I was at the hospital,

38:07.601 --> 38:10.636
I was thinking about you
and what you went through.

38:12.472 --> 38:16.875
And I don't think I ever
quite appreciated that before.

38:16.877 --> 38:19.744
I'm sorry about that.

38:19.746 --> 38:22.281
Noah, don't apologize.

38:22.283 --> 38:23.515
You've been wonderful.

38:23.517 --> 38:25.884
- Have I?
- Yes.

38:29.755 --> 38:31.756
So, anyway,
I got some good news.

38:31.758 --> 38:33.758
- Hmm?
- My divorce, it's done.

38:33.760 --> 38:35.126
It's over.

38:37.529 --> 38:40.065
And that means, uh,
you and I...

38:40.067 --> 38:42.767
Can be together.
It's not an issue anymore.

38:42.769 --> 38:44.702
Helen's agreed
to stop litigating

38:44.704 --> 38:46.870
and give me co-custody,
so...

38:46.872 --> 38:50.307
- [chuckles]
- Hmm. What a relief.

38:52.210 --> 38:54.912
So we're still
a couple then?

38:54.914 --> 38:56.513
What?

38:56.515 --> 38:58.982
Well, we just haven't
seen each other in six weeks.

39:01.119 --> 39:03.087
Alison, we... we couldn't.
The judge said...

39:03.089 --> 39:04.922
Right, I know,
I just, uh...

39:04.924 --> 39:07.191
I hadn't heard from you
for a while,

39:07.193 --> 39:09.426
and I thought you'd just
kinda given up on us.

39:09.428 --> 39:11.695
- We talked all the time.
- Yeah, I know.

39:11.697 --> 39:13.263
- I told you I love you.
- I know.

39:13.265 --> 39:15.098
I was trying to figure out
a way for us to be together.

39:15.100 --> 39:17.601
I read your book, Noah.

39:21.672 --> 39:23.607
[exhales sharply]
What do you mean? How?

39:23.609 --> 39:25.442
It was lying open
on Yvonne's desk

39:25.444 --> 39:26.943
the day I left.

39:30.648 --> 39:31.948
You... did you read
the whole manuscript?

39:31.950 --> 39:33.816
No, just parts of it.

39:33.818 --> 39:37.019
- What parts?
- I'm "sex."

39:37.021 --> 39:39.356
I'm "the reason the word
was invented."

39:39.358 --> 39:41.291
"No marriage
could survive" me.

39:41.293 --> 39:42.859
Is that all you read?

39:42.861 --> 39:45.995
No, I read some choice passages
about my supple breasts,

39:45.997 --> 39:47.996
my perfect ass,

39:47.998 --> 39:49.831
my long tongue on your...

39:49.833 --> 39:52.033
So you... you only read
the sex scenes.

39:52.035 --> 39:53.168
Well, no,
I read a few pages,

39:53.170 --> 39:55.137
but so far as I can tell,

39:55.139 --> 39:56.605
the whole thing
is sex scenes.

39:56.607 --> 39:58.206
That's not true.

39:58.208 --> 39:59.941
I asked you not to read it

39:59.943 --> 40:02.478
because I wanted
to explain it before.

40:02.480 --> 40:04.112
- I wanted you to be prepared.
- For what?

40:04.114 --> 40:05.814
What you really
think of me?

40:05.816 --> 40:09.652
It's fiction.
It's not you. It's not me.

40:09.654 --> 40:11.320
That's what
I wanted to explain.

40:11.322 --> 40:12.921
What? That character
isn't based on me?

40:12.923 --> 40:14.590
[groans]
Characters have a...

40:14.592 --> 40:17.825
they have a life of their own.

40:17.827 --> 40:19.860
I'm sorry you felt bad
about what you read,

40:19.862 --> 40:21.796
but you obviously didn't see
the bigger picture.

40:21.798 --> 40:23.130
- Did you read the ending?
- No.

40:23.132 --> 40:25.667
Well, maybe that's the place
to start.

40:25.669 --> 40:27.602
We end up together.
It's a happy ending.

40:27.604 --> 40:31.972
Wasn't that the end that
Harry wants you to change?

40:31.974 --> 40:35.109
Look, I'm the asshole
in the book.

40:35.111 --> 40:36.977
I destroy everyone
I care about.

40:36.979 --> 40:38.479
I-I ruin my life.

40:38.481 --> 40:39.814
The story's not even
about you.

40:39.816 --> 40:41.949
It's about me.

40:41.951 --> 40:43.418
Before you judge,
will you please

40:43.420 --> 40:46.754
just read the whole book?

40:46.756 --> 40:48.221
No, I won't.

40:50.658 --> 40:53.026
- Why not?
- I just don't want to.

40:54.696 --> 40:57.564
I don't think
it would be a very good idea.

41:08.242 --> 41:10.310
You know, um...

41:10.312 --> 41:14.080
you may be right
about the sex.

41:16.250 --> 41:17.750
About the sex?

41:17.752 --> 41:18.984
Yeah, I've been thinking
a lot about it

41:18.986 --> 41:22.087
since I got here
and, um...

41:22.089 --> 41:26.191
I can see why
you think I'm...

41:26.193 --> 41:27.660
some kind of
nymphomaniac.

41:27.662 --> 41:29.362
I never said that.

41:29.364 --> 41:31.864
No, you met me at
a very strange time in my life,

41:31.866 --> 41:34.066
and I wasn't always...

41:34.068 --> 41:37.002
I used to be
a very open kid,

41:37.004 --> 41:38.738
and since Gabriel died,

41:38.740 --> 41:41.507
I just stopped talking
to people.

41:41.509 --> 41:43.308
I didn't see the point
in it anymore.

41:43.310 --> 41:46.812
They didn't understand,
and, um...

41:46.814 --> 41:49.982
sex for me became a way

41:49.984 --> 41:54.486
of feeling things without
having to talk to anybody.

41:54.488 --> 41:56.688
And then
I guess I...

41:56.690 --> 41:59.190
when I met you,
I'd just gotten used to it.

41:59.192 --> 42:00.759
Used to what?

42:00.761 --> 42:03.828
Well, using reckless behavior
as a way of...

42:03.830 --> 42:07.064
feeling like
I was still alive.

42:07.066 --> 42:09.066
You know, Sebastian thinks
that the cutting

42:09.068 --> 42:10.568
and the reckless sex,

42:10.570 --> 42:11.836
it all stems
from the same impulse.

42:11.838 --> 42:12.937
Who?

42:12.939 --> 42:14.773
Oh, uh, I'm sorry.
Sebastian.

42:14.775 --> 42:16.574
He's a friend of mine
up here.

42:16.576 --> 42:18.710
He's an expert
in reckless behavior?

42:18.712 --> 42:21.780
He is, actually.
He's incredibly brave.

42:21.782 --> 42:24.215
Right.

42:24.217 --> 42:28.552
But, Noah, I haven't had sex
in, like, six weeks,

42:28.554 --> 42:31.388
and...
[sighs]

42:31.390 --> 42:33.089
my head just feels
really clear.

42:33.091 --> 42:36.059
Great. Great.
That's really exciting.

42:36.061 --> 42:39.229
Um, that's something
you're gonna continue

42:39.231 --> 42:40.997
when we leave here?

42:49.006 --> 42:51.708
I got us that place you liked
in Crown Heights.

42:51.710 --> 42:54.110
- The two-bedroom?
- Yeah, I leased it last month.

42:54.112 --> 42:56.747
It's ready for you.
We can go now if you want.

42:56.749 --> 42:58.715
- [laughs] Now?
- Yeah.

42:58.717 --> 43:01.151
Why not? Get your stuff.
Let's get the fuck out of here.

43:01.153 --> 43:02.352
No, I just can't
pick up and leave.

43:02.354 --> 43:04.454
I have a yoga teacher
training class.

43:04.456 --> 43:06.289
- I work in the kitchen.
- Wait...

43:06.291 --> 43:08.291
Living here
was a temporary fix

43:08.293 --> 43:10.460
while I got things
worked out for us.

43:10.462 --> 43:12.362
Well, I like it here.

43:12.364 --> 43:13.964
I'm learning a lot.

43:13.966 --> 43:17.968
Why don't you stay here
with me for a while?

43:17.970 --> 43:19.902
[groans] Oh, God.

43:28.111 --> 43:31.981
[indistinct chanting
in distance]

43:31.983 --> 43:33.349
[bell rings]

43:33.351 --> 43:36.285
[chanting continues]

43:38.188 --> 43:40.556
[bell rings]

43:52.168 --> 43:55.070
[bell ringing,
chanting continues]

44:11.587 --> 44:14.423
[man] <i>The treatment I'm applying</i>
<i>now to this patient</i>

44:14.425 --> 44:18.126
<i>is based on Wilhelm Reich's
orgone therapy,</i>

44:18.128 --> 44:20.628
<i>which releases
biological energy</i>

44:20.630 --> 44:22.897
<i>from chronically constricted
muscles.</i>

44:22.899 --> 44:26.567
<i>You can see, this therapy is
already starting to release</i>

44:26.569 --> 44:28.802
<i>traumatic memories
stored in the patient's body.</i>

44:28.804 --> 44:31.739
<i>- [man breathing heavily]
- Very good.</i>

44:31.741 --> 44:35.043
<i>We mustn't repress.
We must liberate.</i>

44:35.045 --> 44:37.978
[birds chirping]

44:48.389 --> 44:50.657
Oh, fuck!

45:04.104 --> 45:06.105
[Athena]
And so our flaws are actually

45:06.107 --> 45:08.007
the source of our strength.

45:08.009 --> 45:10.944
That focused meditation
was so powerful.

45:10.946 --> 45:13.312
- Thank you for your gifts.
- Oh, you're so welcome.

45:13.314 --> 45:15.682
I felt my Level Two
attune automatically.

45:15.684 --> 45:17.850
I did too.
That was remarkable.

45:19.486 --> 45:22.254
Noah!

45:22.256 --> 45:26.091
So you're... you're experiencing
some writer's block?

45:26.093 --> 45:27.859
That must be
frightening for you.

45:27.861 --> 45:30.829
No, I'm... no, I'm trying to find
a place to write, Athena.

45:30.831 --> 45:32.631
- It's different.
- Oh.

45:32.633 --> 45:34.967
I was under the impression
you'd been having difficulty

45:34.969 --> 45:37.469
with your ending
for a while now.

45:37.471 --> 45:39.237
Don't worry about it.
It'll be fine.

45:39.239 --> 45:42.073
I just need to get Alison
and get the hell out of here.

45:42.075 --> 45:45.109
Isn't it miraculous
how balanced she's become

45:45.111 --> 45:46.944
since she's been here?

45:46.946 --> 45:49.780
She's moving in such harmony
with the universe.

45:49.782 --> 45:51.616
That must be
such a relief for you.

45:51.618 --> 45:54.585
Having only known her
in a state of...

45:54.587 --> 45:56.621
such dysfunction.

45:56.623 --> 45:57.622
[sarcastically] Sure is.

45:57.624 --> 45:59.123
[chuckles]

45:59.125 --> 46:01.926
I sense some sarcasm.

46:03.561 --> 46:04.928
No offense, Athena...
I just don't think

46:04.930 --> 46:06.330
any of this is real.

46:06.332 --> 46:08.332
Nothing is real, Noah.

46:08.334 --> 46:10.134
It's easy to feel at peace

46:10.136 --> 46:11.735
when you're just eating quinoa
all day

46:11.737 --> 46:15.172
and sleeping 14 hours,
but in the real world, I...

46:15.174 --> 46:17.474
I don't think you're doing her
any favors keeping her here.

46:17.476 --> 46:18.742
I see now.

46:18.744 --> 46:21.845
Yes, it's suddenly so clear,

46:21.847 --> 46:23.180
so expected of course.

46:23.182 --> 46:24.481
What?

46:24.483 --> 46:26.750
You fell in love
with her darkness.

46:26.752 --> 46:28.385
Now that she's stepping
into the light,

46:28.387 --> 46:30.153
you feel like you're losing
your hold on her.

46:30.155 --> 46:31.720
My what?

46:31.722 --> 46:33.889
That speaks to your primal fear
of abandonment.

46:33.891 --> 46:36.659
You know what, Athena?
Just shove it. Okay?

46:36.661 --> 46:39.328
I-I... how the fuck
do I get out of here?

46:39.330 --> 46:42.532
- Fuck!
- Noah, this is good.

46:42.534 --> 46:44.833
You're beginning to access
your rage. That's a vital step.

46:44.835 --> 46:46.335
Why don't you come in
for a session?

46:46.337 --> 46:47.670
I've had great success

46:47.672 --> 46:49.505
with writers and artists
using Reiki.

46:49.507 --> 46:50.706
- Oh, fuck that.
- I would be happy to work

46:50.708 --> 46:52.374
with you, as my gift,

46:52.376 --> 46:54.743
to unlock the flow
of your creative energy.

47:07.423 --> 47:08.957
[Alison]
<i>In Afghanistan?</i>

47:08.959 --> 47:10.793
Yeah, I was there
before 9/11.

47:10.795 --> 47:12.427
I was with
the Northern Alliance,

47:12.429 --> 47:14.128
and they'd just taken
this hilltop position...

47:14.130 --> 47:16.898
- Hey, Alison.
- Oh, hey.

47:16.900 --> 47:19.433
Oh, I'm glad you're here.
Uh, I wanted you guys to meet.

47:19.435 --> 47:23.104
This is Sebastian.
This is Noah, uh, my friend.

47:23.106 --> 47:24.939
And, um...

47:24.941 --> 47:27.075
Noah, this is Sebastian.

47:29.078 --> 47:30.611
S-Sebastian Junger?

47:30.613 --> 47:32.714
Nice to meet you, Noah.

47:32.716 --> 47:34.882
[stammers]

47:34.884 --> 47:36.750
<i>Perfect Storm,</i>
I read it in 48 hours,

47:36.752 --> 47:39.119
and <i>War</i> was incredible.

47:39.121 --> 47:40.754
Thank you.
I'm glad you like my work.

47:40.756 --> 47:42.622
This is the last place
I'd expect to find you.

47:42.624 --> 47:44.091
[Sebastian laughs]
I'm here all the time.

47:44.093 --> 47:46.392
As much as I can be.

47:46.394 --> 47:48.294
Did you get any work done
this afternoon?

47:48.296 --> 47:51.098
No, no. I-I can't find anywhere
to concentrate.

47:51.100 --> 47:52.733
Is there anywhere here
you can write?

47:52.735 --> 47:54.400
I can write
pretty much anywhere.

47:54.402 --> 47:55.736
[laughs]

47:55.738 --> 47:58.138
Right, well,
of course you can.

47:58.140 --> 47:59.572
Sounds like
you're kinda blocked.

47:59.574 --> 48:02.709
You know what helps me?
Reiki.

48:06.947 --> 48:09.949
[peaceful music plays on stereo]

48:09.951 --> 48:13.786
♪

48:13.788 --> 48:16.789
[clears throat]

48:16.791 --> 48:21.794
♪

48:21.796 --> 48:24.764
We're gonna work
on your chakras,

48:24.766 --> 48:26.799
where the channels
of energy

48:26.801 --> 48:30.069
which run through
your subtle body meet.

48:35.142 --> 48:37.376
Is this something you have
to believe in for it to work?

48:37.378 --> 48:38.843
Quite the opposite.

48:38.845 --> 48:41.613
The treatment itself
will guide you toward belief.

48:44.049 --> 48:47.618
- Good, 'cause I don't think...
- Shh.

48:47.620 --> 48:50.321
[sighs]

48:50.323 --> 48:55.225
♪

48:56.695 --> 48:58.862
Ah.

48:58.864 --> 49:01.532
[quickly exhales sharply]

49:12.877 --> 49:14.178
Hmm.

49:14.180 --> 49:16.847
This is your root chakra.

49:16.849 --> 49:20.551
It governs sexuality,
sensuality,

49:20.553 --> 49:22.920
as well as stability.

49:22.922 --> 49:27.124
♪

49:27.126 --> 49:30.460
As you can see for yourself,
there's a creative blockage.

49:32.163 --> 49:36.099
Your Kundalini,
your primal energy,

49:36.101 --> 49:40.403
has become trapped between
your pull toward darkness

49:40.405 --> 49:44.607
and your need
to seek stability in life.

49:44.609 --> 49:47.610
We need to release
your Kundalini from this limbo.

49:47.612 --> 49:49.612
[exhales slowly]

49:49.614 --> 49:51.681
Liberate it to flow upward

49:51.683 --> 49:54.151
towards your place
of consciousness.

49:58.222 --> 50:01.123
- [exhaling sharply]
- [groans]

50:07.030 --> 50:09.499
Please turn
onto your stomach.

50:11.068 --> 50:12.635
Go on.

50:15.439 --> 50:18.207
Good. Good.

50:21.512 --> 50:24.848
You are drawn
to the darkness in others,

50:24.850 --> 50:28.885
but at the same time,
you fear it.

50:28.887 --> 50:31.186
You're afraid
it will consume you,

50:31.188 --> 50:33.889
will obliterate
your carefully crafted image,

50:33.891 --> 50:37.393
it will expose you
as a fraud, but, Noah,

50:37.395 --> 50:41.329
until you let yourself
experience your baser desire,

50:41.331 --> 50:45.166
you will never be able
to hear your true voice.

50:45.168 --> 50:46.101
[exhales sharply]

50:48.571 --> 50:51.039
[exhales sharply]

50:51.041 --> 50:54.109
Let the darkness in.
Let the darkness in.

50:54.111 --> 50:59.515
[echoing] Let your root energy
flow through you.

50:59.517 --> 51:01.750
<i>When it meets your place
of true insight,</i>

51:01.752 --> 51:03.919
you will experience
a moment of consciousness

51:03.921 --> 51:05.754
free from all illusion.

51:05.756 --> 51:08.923
<i>The self will fall away,</i>

51:08.925 --> 51:13.327
and, at last,
you will see everything.

51:13.329 --> 51:16.130
<i>Let the darkness in.</i>

51:16.132 --> 51:17.364
[screams]

51:22.905 --> 51:25.139
[yoga instructor]
<i>Exhale. Press your hands down.</i>

51:25.141 --> 51:27.975
Alison.

51:27.977 --> 51:30.010
- Can we talk?
- Exhale.

51:30.012 --> 51:31.979
Outside.
Can we talk now?

51:31.981 --> 51:35.115
- Please. Come on.
- Noah.

51:35.117 --> 51:37.918
What's wrong with you?

51:37.920 --> 51:39.453
What is wrong with you?

51:39.455 --> 51:41.588
I spent the last six weeks
doing everything I promised

51:41.590 --> 51:42.823
so that we could be together,

51:42.825 --> 51:44.258
which is what I thought
you wanted too.

51:44.260 --> 51:46.327
- Do you want that?
- Yes, of course I do.

51:46.329 --> 51:48.562
Well, then stop flaking out
at this stupid summer camp,

51:48.564 --> 51:50.730
- and let's get out of here.
- I have commitments.

51:50.732 --> 51:52.999
Really? Like your commitment
to Sebastian Junger?

51:53.001 --> 51:54.934
How the fuck did you get
so close to him anyway?

51:54.936 --> 51:56.436
Oh, for God's sakes, Noah.

51:56.438 --> 51:59.839
I blew up my life for you,
Alison, and now here I am,

51:59.841 --> 52:01.207
wanting to leave with you,
and you can't leave

52:01.209 --> 52:02.508
because you got
a fucking yoga class?

52:02.510 --> 52:03.709
Look, I am just as committed

52:03.711 --> 52:05.578
to this relationship
as you are, Noah!

52:05.580 --> 52:08.014
I don't belong to you.
We're not living in your book.

52:08.016 --> 52:09.983
You can't control me.

52:09.985 --> 52:12.017
[breathing heavily]

52:12.019 --> 52:13.953
No?

52:32.305 --> 52:34.740
[gasps]

52:34.742 --> 52:37.676
[grunting]

52:53.526 --> 52:56.461
[breathing heavily]

53:50.048 --> 53:52.816
I'm pregnant.

